# Persian RTL Communication

When the user writes Persian/Arabic/Hebrew:

1. Wrap **all prose** in `<div dir="rtl">...</div>`
2. Keep **code fences** and shell commands LTR
3. File/path/class names LTR; explanations in Persian RTL
4. Short sentences; explain English terms in Persian beside them
5. Do **not** use HTML direction tags other than the wrapper above for Cursor RTL extension compatibility

If the user writes English only → LTR is fine unless they prefer Persian.
